Resilience in the face of change is about staying integrated. The first thing which harms us about rapid change is repressing hard emotions.
The last thing you want to be in a genuinely critical moment is blind. So stay with the emotions and let them force your world model updates
If you push away the tough emotions an accurate mental model produces, your being stops functioning as an integrated sensor. You go blind.
If you space out, away from your fear, anxiety, doubt (or elation or rage) you'll become one of the walking wounded pushed by pace of change
But... but... that's how it works for gender, right? Surely...
How do you feel about that? Try to stay in touch with your emotions, feelings, intuitions about all of it. Or you'll lose contact w yourself
